# PhotogrammetrySession.Configuration.CustomDetailSpecification.TextureDimension

**Enumeration**

One of the discrete texture dimensions to specify the size of the model texture maps. For example, a `.twoK` dimension means the texture map size can be up to size 2048x2048.

## Declaration

```swift
enum TextureDimension
```

## Enumeration Cases

- **PhotogrammetrySession.Configuration.CustomDetailSpecification.TextureDimension.eightK**
- **PhotogrammetrySession.Configuration.CustomDetailSpecification.TextureDimension.fourK**

- **PhotogrammetrySession.Configuration.CustomDetailSpecification.TextureDimension.sixteenK**
- **PhotogrammetrySession.Configuration.CustomDetailSpecification.TextureDimension.twoK**
